'''Dothideomycetes''' is a [[class (biology)|class]] of [[ascomycete]] [[fungi]]. It comprises about 50 families, 650 genera and 6300 known species. Traditionally most of its members were included in the clade [[Loculoascomycetes]]. The class contains several important [[Phytopathology|plant pathogens]] (like ''[[Phaeosphaeria nodorum]]'' and ''[[Venturia inaequalis]]'').

